# TodoMVC Architecture Plan

## 1) Module structure and file organization

- `src/main.tsx`: app bootstrap.
- `src/App.tsx`: root composition (layout + context + routed filter state).
- `src/styles/`: global styles and imported official TodoMVC CSS wiring.
- `src/types/todo.ts`: `Todo` domain type.
- `src/types/filter.ts`: filter enum/union and route mapping.
- `src/state/todosReducer.ts`: pure reducer + action definitions.
- `src/state/selectors.ts`: derived data (`activeCount`, `completedCount`, filtered list).
- `src/persistence/todosStorage.ts`: localStorage read/write + migration/validation.
- `src/context/TodosContext.tsx`: provider + hook exposing state/actions.
- `src/components/Header.tsx`: new-todo input and submit handling.
- `src/components/TodoItem.tsx`: toggle/edit/destroy behavior.
- `src/components/Main.tsx`: list rendering + toggle-all.
- `src/components/Footer.tsx`: counts, filters, clear-completed.
- `src/router/filterRouter.ts`: hash route <-> filter conversion.
- `src/test/setup.ts`: Vitest/RTL setup.
- `src/test/e2e/`: end-to-end TodoMVC spec tests.
- `docker/Dockerfile` and `docker/nginx.conf`: production container and static serving.

## 2) Shared types and contracts

- `Todo`: `{ id: string; title: string; completed: boolean; createdAt?: number }`.
- `Filter`: `all | active | completed` (enum or string-literal union).
- Reducer actions (discriminated union):
  - add, toggle, toggleAll, remove, editTitle, clearCompleted, hydrate.
- Context contract:
  - `state`: todos + current filter
  - `actions`: reducer-backed dispatch helpers
  - `selectors`: counts + filteredTodos
- Persistence contract:
  - only todos persisted (filter derived from router)
  - safe parse + schema guard + fallback to empty list.

## 3) Issue dependency order

- Foundations: #1 -> #2 -> #3 -> #4 -> #5 -> #6
- Domain/state core: #7 -> #8 -> #9 -> #10
- UI components: #11 and #12 -> #13 -> #14
- Routing/composition: #15 -> #16
- Quality gates: #17 -> #18 -> #19

Cross-dependencies:
- #8 depends on #7.
- #9 depends on #7 and reducer state shape from #8.
- #10 depends on #8/#9.
- #13 depends on #12 and context from #10.
- #14 depends on #13 selectors and filter type from #7/#15.
- #16 depends on #10/#11/#13/#14/#15.
- #17 depends on a fully integrated #16.
- #18 depends on implemented UI and keyboard flows (#11-#16).
- #19 depends on test/build + docker setup (#5/#6/#17/#18).

## 4) Key design decisions

- Keep reducer pure and side effects out; persistence happens in provider via `useEffect`.
- Use typed action creators to prevent invalid dispatch payloads.
- Store routing filter in URL hash to match TodoMVC behavior and keep shareable state.
- Centralize derived state in selectors to avoid duplicated logic across components.
- Prefer controlled editing input in `TodoItem` with explicit commit/cancel keyboard semantics.
- Add test pyramid:
  - reducer unit tests,
  - component behavior tests (RTL),
  - e2e TodoMVC spec coverage.
- Container image is static build served by nginx (multi-stage, minimal runtime).
